import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the x-coordinates of the points?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_numeric(data['x'], errors='coerce')
    data['y'] = pd.to_numeric(data['y'], errors='coerce')
    dists = pdist(data[['x', 'y']])
    dists = squareform(dists)
    sns.heatmap(dists, cmap='coolwarm', square=True, cbar_kws={'label': 'Distance'})
    plt.title('What is the average distance between the points?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=dists.mean(), color='black', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean distance: {dists.mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
